01.10 COMMENT PROJECTILE TRAJECTORY AND ENERGY TABLE
01.20 COMMENT INPUT SPEED ANGLE MASS AND TIME STEP
01.30 ASK V
01.40 ASK A
01.50 ASK M
01.60 ASK D
01.70 SET G=9.80665
01.80 SET X=V*COS(A)
01.90 SET Y=V*SIN(A)
02.10 SET F=2*Y/G
02.20 SET R=X*F
02.30 SET H=Y^2/(2*G)
02.40 SET K=M*V^2/2
02.50 COMMENT FLIGHT TIME RANGE HEIGHT ENERGY
02.60 PRINT F,!,R,!,H,!,K
02.70 COMMENT TABLE COLUMNS TIME X Y SPEED ENERGY
02.80 FOR T=0,D,F; DO 3
02.90 EXIT
03.10 SET P=X*T
03.20 SET Q=Y*T-G*T^2/2
03.30 SET U=Y-G*T
03.40 SET S=SQRT(X^2+U^2)
03.50 SET E=M*S^2/2
03.60 PRINT T,P,Q,S,E,!
03.70 RETURN
04.10 COMMENT THE TABLE INCLUDES LAUNCH AND LANDING
04.20 COMMENT USE RADIAN DEGREE OR GRADE SWITCH
04.30 COMMENT NEGATIVE FINAL HEIGHT MEANS STEP IS TOO LARGE
04.40 COMMENT SMALLER STEP GIVES A SMOOTHER TRAJECTORY
04.50 COMMENT HORIZONTAL VELOCITY REMAINS CONSTANT
04.60 COMMENT VERTICAL VELOCITY FALLS WITH ELAPSED TIME
04.70 COMMENT MASS CHANGES ENERGY BUT DOES NOT CHANGE PATH
04.80 COMMENT AIR RESISTANCE WIND LIFT CURVATURE ARE IGNORED
04.90 COMMENT THIS MODEL IS FOR SHORT EDUCATIONAL FLIGHTS
